Steps to host your DC bot on Heroku:

Create an account on Heroku.

  Install the Heroku CLI (Command Line Interface) on your local machine.

  Log in to your Heroku account using the CLI.

  Create a new app on Heroku, this will create a new remote repository.

  Commit your code to the newly created repository, you can use git to do that.

  Configure the environment variables, this includes your bot token, it's important to keep the token private.

  Deploy the code to Heroku by pushing the code to the remote repository.

  Scale the app, you can use the Heroku CLI or the web interface to do that.

Your bot should be up and running now.
